description:
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Health Foundation Trust consists of Frimley Park Hospital, Wexham Park Hospital and Heatherwood Hospital, we are one of the country&#39;s largest and most respected hospital trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and exceptional senior nursing leader with a strong background in operational management. You will lead across a portfolio of clinical areas within the Paediatric directorate, with the main focus of the role being the Paediatric and Neonatal services. You will have the ability to take services for our patients and carers to a new level of excellence and performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will hold line management responsibility and lead the nursing teams in delivering care within the Paediatric Wards, Paediatric assessment units, Paediatric Outpatient areas as well as our Neonatal Units. You will also support the Chief of Service and Associate Director to achieve operational and strategic objectives and have a key role in the triumvirate management team within the directorate. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a dynamic, enthusiastic, motivated and forward thinking experienced Paediatric or Neonatology nurse who has developed their clinical and management skills and can demonstrate excellent leadership skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amy Olley - a.olley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rekha Sanghavi - Chief of service Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
